#FIPS: is the column labeling the county so that the data becomes easily accessible and organized. We need this when we want to analysize votes, as it shows ur who is voting where - numeric
#Canidate: Shows which politician is getting the votes in a county. Helps us measure how diffrent people behave in different places - Catergorical
#Year: Allows future generations to analyse the data based on the year. It helps give a histrocial setting - numeric
#TotalVotes: Helpes us measure the percent vote a canidate has received - numeric
#CanidateVotes: How mnay votes a politician has received in a county - numeric

#2.
df2.head(10)
#Total_population: Helps us analyse how big a county is, and lets us see if views are very similar in condensed popluations - numeric
#White_pct: The race given the most priviledge in society. Lets us see how the canidates effect different races - numeric
#Female_Pct: Allows us to view how gender effects votes - numeric
#Foreign_born_pct: Allows us to question whether imigrants hold diiferent views than other born citizens - numeric
#Median_household_income: How do the middle class vote in relation to other poeple of different social and econiomic status - numeric

df2.pop("st")
#This column is repetitive thus deleting is fine
df2['hispanic_pct'].fillna(df2['black_and_hispanic_pct']-df2["black_pct"], inplace=True )
df2['black_pct'].fillna(df2['black_and_hispanic_pct']-df2["hispanic_pct"], inplace=True )
#I used this to determine the remaining poplution of the hispanic and black poeple by subtracting their total. 
df2['black_pct'] = df2['black_pct'].fillna(df2['black_pct'].mean())
df2['hispanic_pct'] = df2['hispanic_pct'].fillna(df2['hispanic_pct'].mean())
#We must also take into account the possibility that the total plus required race pct is missing, 
#hence we can add the average null filler after the previous command is finished
df2['county'] = df2['county'].fillna("Not Specified")
#A small percent of counties were unnamed, intead of deleting them, we can name them "Not specified".

#Generally, nulls with a percentage of 5 and above are usually needed to be dealth with in a proper manner, 
#but 2.4% is fairly close, hence we can deal with the citizen column as well
# for citizen voting age pop, we can take the total population and divide it by voting age pop *100 to find the percentage. 
#We can use this percanteg to fill in all the null vals, by doing percent * total pop
#This formula only works for columns that already have total popluation filled in, thus we can fill the nulls 
#for this column using the averge first
df2['total_population'] = df2['total_population'].fillna(1.019768e+05)
df2 = df2.assign(num=0)
#creates a new temp column 
df2['num'] = df2['citizen_voting_age_population']/df2['total_population']
df2['citizen_voting_age_population'].fillna(df2['total_population']*df2['num'].mean(),inplace=True)
del df2['num']
#deletes the column after use, as it is not needed

#the remianing columns all have null percentages of 0.128452, which is very little thus ignorable. 
#Instead of keeping these null values, we can fill them in with the average as it will help keep the 
#data intergity (if columns are not deleted)
df2['black_and_hispanic_pct'] = df2['black_and_hispanic_pct'].fillna(17.939017)
df2['nonwhite_pct'] = df2['nonwhite_pct'].fillna(22.623601)
df2['foreign_born_pct'] = df2['foreign_born_pct'].fillna(4.614669)
df2['female_pct'] = df2['female_pct'].fillna(49.975212)
df2['caucasian_frac'] = df2['caucasian_frac'].fillna(0.773756)
df2['age_29_and_under_pct'] = df2['age_29_and_under_pct'].fillna(37.340978)
df2['age_65_and_older_pct'] = df2['age_65_and_older_pct'].fillna(17.636371)
df2['median_household_income'] = df2['median_household_income'].fillna(47809.562058)
df2['unemployed_pct_in_civilian_labor_force'] = df2['unemployed_pct_in_civilian_labor_force'].fillna(7.063559)
df2['less_than_highschool_pct'] = df2['less_than_highschool_pct'].fillna(14.226943)
df2['less_than_college_pct'] = df2['less_than_college_pct'].fillna(79.227596)
df2['rural population_pct'] = df2['rural population_pct'].fillna(58.489157)
df2['white_pct'] = df2['white_pct'].fillna(77.376399)
df2.isna().mean()*100
